"v.不许，禁止；妨碍，阻止 【英】 v. 不许,禁止(order sb not to do sth);妨碍,阻止(make sth difficult or impossible ) 【考】 反义词： countenance(支持) 【例】 Lack of space forbids further treatment of the topic here. v. 禁止; 妨碍; 阻止 = prohibit = preclude 【参】forbidding(adj 可怕的: 企图威胁阻止进展的; 令人难亲近的) 【反】countenance(v 赞助; 支持n 面容) 无 forbid (v.)  Old English forbeodan ""forbid, prohibit,"" from for- ""against"" + beodan ""to command"" (see bid). Common Germanic compound (cognates: Dutch verbieden, Old High German farbiotan, German verbieten, Old Norse fyrirbjoða, Gothic faurbiudan ""to forbid""). Related: Forbade; forbidden."
